content: Changed my rating. Haven't been able to use it for a week.

Also uploading images used to work great, now it just freezes up.  You should just do what everyone else does and allow thumbprint to sign in.  There's also 0 reason you need location permissions for this app. --- Edit after reply from developer: Months ago I emailed you guys about this problem and you were no help in resolving.  This is a business application.  It needs to work.  Obviously from the comments, I'm not the only person having the issues.

content: Downloaded and can't even log in without allowing it multiple permissions. Most apps allow you to deny permissions, then when the app actually needs to access them it will ask again. This one when you deny, you can't log in at all. Okay, I understand photo/media, if you can deposit checks from the app. Maybe call from app feature, I assume this is so you can call the help desk from the app, not necessary, but I understand. I draw the line at my location. There is no instance that I feel the bank needs to know my GPS location. Considering this is a feature I leave off on my phone unless I'm using Maps, I do not think it is okay for a bank to have unlimited access to turn it on as they wish.  CHANGE YOUR PERMISSIONS!!! THEY SHOULD NOT BE REQUIRED TO LOG IN, ONLY REQUIRED WHEN YOU ATTEMPT TO USE RELATED FEATURES.
